<h1>@HI{{to iu @KJ{{idea^flavor}}}}</h1>

<h2> Formation </h2>

<ol>
<li> X@HI{{ha <strong>to iu @KJ{{idea^flavor}}</strong>desu}}
</ol>

<h2> Definition </h2>

<p>
This pattern is used to ask the meaning of the word or phrase represented by "X".
</p>

<h2> Examples </h2>

<ol>
<li>
<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KJ{{stand*up^enter^prohibition^stop}}a @KJ{{enter}}runa<strong>to iu @KJ{{idea^flavor}}desu.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      "Tachiri-Kinshi" means don't enter.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</ol>

<h2> Notes </h2>

Compared with @Vyou{{}} @HI{{to @KJ{{think}}tteimasu}}, @Vru{{}} @HI{{<strong>to iu @KJ{{idea^flavor}}</strong>desu.}} sounds more determined.
